<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1324,1756,1902]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,446,1756,1782]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Description.—</emphasis>
Male. Body length 
<quantity box="[683,794,1756,1782]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.94" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="4.94">4.94 mm</quantity>
; LFW 3.0 mm. Color: head and mesosoma black, except pronotum dark castaneous, metasoma rufous castaneous, mandible and antenna castaneous, palpi, tegula and legs yellowish castaneous, wings hyaline, veins castaneous.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158461/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" targetBox="[323,1297,324,1395]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1323,1425,1518]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,448,1425,1449]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">FIGURE 14–19.</emphasis>
14–16, 
<taxonomicName box="[537,701,1426,1449]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lapsa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[537,701,1426,1449]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Apenesia 
<taxonomicName box="[643,701,1426,1449]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species" species="lapsa" status="sp. nov.">lapsa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[708,794,1425,1449]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[708,794,1425,1449]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
14, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 15 mandible, frontal view; 16, genitalia, ventral view 17–19, 
<taxonomicName box="[815,965,1461,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[815,965,1461,1484]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Apenesia 
<taxonomicName box="[919,965,1461,1484]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species" species="acia" status="sp. nov.">acia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[971,1056,1460,1484]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[971,1056,1460,1484]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
17, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 18 mandible, frontal view; 19, genitalia, ventral view (Scale bars = 1 mm).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1323,1569,1876]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,379,1569,1595]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[401,495,1570,1596]" captionStart="FIGURE 14 – 19. 14 – 16" captionStartId="9.[264,368,1425,1449]" captionTargetBox="[323,1297,324,1395]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[294,1314,299,1396]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 14 – 19. 14 – 16, Apenesia lapsa sp. nov. 14, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 15 mandible, frontal view; 16, genitalia, ventral view 17 – 19, Apenesia acia sp. nov. 17, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 18 mandible, frontal view; 19, genitalia, ventral view (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158461/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[462,495,1570,1596]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
): mandibles with five large teeth (
<figureCitation box="[931,1024,1570,1596]" captionStart="FIGURE 14 – 19. 14 – 16" captionStartId="9.[264,368,1425,1449]" captionTargetBox="[323,1297,324,1395]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[294,1314,299,1396]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 14 – 19. 14 – 16, Apenesia lapsa sp. nov. 14, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 15 mandible, frontal view; 16, genitalia, ventral view 17 – 19, Apenesia acia sp. nov. 17, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 18 mandible, frontal view; 19, genitalia, ventral view (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158461/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[992,1024,1570,1596]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Clypeus with truncate median lobe with rounded corners, median carina very high and angled in profile. First four antennal segments in a ratio of 
<number box="[701,736,1650,1676]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="40.0">40</number>
: 
<number box="[740,755,1650,1676]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="9.0">9</number>
: 
<number box="[759,792,1650,1676]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="28.0">28</number>
: 
<number box="[796,830,1650,1676]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="30.0">30</number>
, segment III 
<number box="[990,1027,1650,1676]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2.8">2.8</number>
X as long as thick, segment XI 
<number box="[371,422,1690,1716]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="3.57">3.57</number>
X as long as thick. Eyes glabrous. Frons polished, with conspicuous punctures, absent near the toruli and eyes. WH 
<number box="[759,795,1730,1756]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="0.9">0.9</number>
X LH; WF 
<number box="[936,973,1730,1756]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="0.6">0.6</number>
X WH, WF 
<number box="[1121,1173,1730,1756]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1.12">1.12</number>
X HE; OOL 
<number box="[264,301,1770,1796]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1.7">1.7</number>
X WOT; frontal angle of ocellar triangle acute; distance from the posterior ocelli to vertex crest 
<number box="[407,443,1810,1836]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X 
<collectingCountry box="[480,547,1810,1836]" name="Iceland" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15671" box="[480,547,1810,1836]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15671" name="Agriculture and Agri-Food Canada" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">DAO</collectionCode>
</collectingCountry>
. Vertex barely convex, corners rounded, occipital carina visible in dorsal view. VOL 
<number box="[480,531,1850,1876]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="0.66">0.66</number>
X HE.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1324,283,1193]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,444,283,309]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Mesosoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[460,549,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURE 14 – 19. 14 – 16" captionStartId="9.[264,368,1425,1449]" captionTargetBox="[323,1297,324,1395]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[294,1314,299,1396]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 14 – 19. 14 – 16, Apenesia lapsa sp. nov. 14, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 15 mandible, frontal view; 16, genitalia, ventral view 17 – 19, Apenesia acia sp. nov. 17, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 18 mandible, frontal view; 19, genitalia, ventral view (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158461/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[516,549,284,310]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
): thorax polished. Pronotal disc with anterior carina. Notauli well impressed, incomplete anteriorly. Parapsidal furrows incomplete anteriorly. Propodeal disc 
<number box="[264,314,364,390]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1.33">1.33</number>
X as wide as long, basal triangle and longitudinal ridges, otherwise polished, declivity without median carina.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1324,283,1193]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,442,443,469]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Metasoma</emphasis>
: petiolate, petiole very short 
<number box="[793,830,444,470]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="0.1">0.1</number>
X as long as the tergite I. Genitalia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 14 – 19. 14 – 16" captionStartId="9.[264,368,1425,1449]" captionTargetBox="[323,1297,324,1395]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[294,1314,299,1396]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 14 – 19. 14 – 16, Apenesia lapsa sp. nov. 14, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 15 mandible, frontal view; 16, genitalia, ventral view 17 – 19, Apenesia acia sp. nov. 17, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 18 mandible, frontal view; 19, genitalia, ventral view (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158461/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[264,297,484,510]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
): paramere short, 
<number box="[512,563,484,510]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="0.58">0.58</number>
X as long as the basiparamere, apical margin strongly concave, inner portion rounded and somewhat shorter than outer corner, the latter angulate; volsella with the ventral ramus of digitus moderately wide and high, 
<number box="[971,1008,564,590]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="0.5">0.5</number>
X as long as the paramere, apex rounded, inner margin somewhat angulate and the outer straight; aedeagus with two pairs of apical lobes, the apex of lateral pair directed downward, with the outer corner rounded and the inner angled, base of the lobes with inner margin strongly constricted, the median pair small, thin and slightly directed upward.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
